node.text:
This morning I woke up with a new sense of hope for a more united America. As a mom, this election took on a whole new meaning – I think about my son’s future and the future of every child in our country. Watching the dignity, power and grace @kamalaharris exudes as our first female VP-elect brought me joy for all women, but especially the black and brown girls who will now see themselves reflected in a way they haven’t ever before. Regardless of who you voted for, this moment is an opportunity to reflect and reset as we look toward building a better tomorrow, together. 

Voice of @vanjones68 
🎥: @julianmarshall

node.text: Becoming a mother has given me so much purpose and appreciation for my strengths (and the strength of EVERY mom), but mom shaming is still an incredibly toxic part of the experience. Every type of shaming is hurtful and wrong, but mom shaming gets to me in a different way. It makes us question the one thing we are most worried about - setting our children up to be happy and healthy. Thank you @jadapinkettsmith @willowsmith @adriennebanfieldnorris for having me on @redtabletalk and pushing this conversation. I hope we all continue to talk about this and learn to lead with empathy and understanding. We’re all trying to do our best! ❤️ What has been a mom shaming experience you’ve had and how did you cope?

node.title: Talking Mom Shaming on Red Table Talk

node.text: It’s season 2! Every day for the next five days I’m going to be dropping a new workout targeting a different area! Last season I was very pregnant and when I filmed this season I was 7 months postpartum. After going through all those changes I wanted to show you new approachable workouts that can meet you WHEREVER you’re at and help you learn to love your body. Soooo...who’s ready to THANK 🙏 BOD ❤️ Follow along from the link in my bioooo 😉 and tag me in your Thank Bod challenge posts all week!

node.text:
I’ve been a fan of podcasts for a while now and lately I have been LOVING listening to them while I’m at home, whether it’s learning new things while attempting to cook or just winding down. Annnddd since I’m so excited to talk about some of my faves I teamed up with @Spotify to host a 3-part podcast talk, #ListenUpWithAshleyGraham. Come back here for the discussion topics, and check out Spotify’s For The Record blog (link in bio: Spotify.com/AshleyGraham) for all the details. Join me on IG Live 8/26 at 12PM EST for the first talk. See you there!

@Spotify @SpotifyPodcasts #SpotifyPartner
